  "text": "MUT could be beneficial in individuals with rare germline KCNJ5 mutations who do not respond to therapy with mineralocorticoid antagonists and would otherwise require bilateral adrenalectomy [CITATION_1] . For long-term use, antibiotic and gastrointestinal effects would need to be eliminated from such a drug. Our studies indicate that channel inhibition can be separated from these other effects, affording promise that such inhibitors can be developed.",
